'''William Barron''' (1837 – 16 June 1916) was a 19th-century [[Member of Parliament]] from [[Dunedin]], New Zealand.

Born in [[St Andrews]], Scotland in 1837, Barron arrived in New Zealand in 1851. He first spent time as a miner and merchant on the Otago goldfields before engaging in business in Dunedin. He served as Grand Master of the New Zealand Lodge of Freemasons.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&cl=search&d=ODT19160617.2.101 | title=Obituary: Mr Wm. Barron | date=17 June 1916 | work=Otago Daily Times | accessdate=15 March 2014 | page=12}}</ref>

He represented the [[Caversham (New Zealand electorate)|Caversham]] electorate from 1879 to 1890, when he retired.<ref name="Wilson">
{{cite book |last= Wilson |first= James Oakley |title= New Zealand parliamentary record, 1840-1984 |edition= 4 |origyear= First ed. published 1913 |year= 1985 |publisher= V.R. Ward, Govt. Printer |location= Wellington |isbn= |oclc= 154283103 |page=182 |pages= }}</ref>

